27/01/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Counterterrorism activities are among the key police priorities this year, according to Police Chief Giorgos Angelakos. 
He met on Wednesday (26 January) with Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis and top interior ministry officials. 
According to Angelakos, efforts will also be focused on reducing the crime rate, particularly in Athens. 
(Kathimerini - 27/01/05)
